<subSubSection box="[198,1291,1942,1966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1734,2035]" box="[198,1291,1942,1966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis box="[198,326,1942,1966]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1942,1966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bellamy" authorityYear="2008" box="[549,654,1943,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Madecorformica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silhouetta">
<emphasis box="[549,654,1943,1966]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">silhouetta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is chosen for the elytral pattern of facing heads on the disc.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1734,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis box="[198,309,1977,2001]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,302,1977,2001]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Remarks</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This new species differs, and can be distinguished, from other lookalike, putative ant-mimics of the genus 
<emphasis box="[151,301,2012,2035]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Entomogaster</emphasis>
as noted in 
<tableCitation box="[429,508,2012,2035]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,241,567,591]" captionText="TABLE 1. Diagnostic character states for Entomogaster and Madecorformica." pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
